#1 Status-post R1 resection for recurrent colon adenocarcinoma in the retroperitoneum
Basic cancer education has been provided to the patient at the request of Dr. Skinner service.  I have had the opportunity to review the operative report, surgical pathology, laboratory values, and notes in Documents Browser.  I have reviewed these findings with the patient and answered questions.  I have discussed this case in detail with Dr. Pichardo, my collaborating physician, who has guided my plan.
We have discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including the type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status, and stage of the cancer.
We recommend that Mr. Schrupp receive chemotherapy.  He does not plan on returning in the outpatient setting for formal evaluation, and therefore, I will ask Dr. Pichardo to visit with him prior to dismissal for formal treatment evaluation.  I informed him that if the need arises in the future, we would be more than happy to help facilitate care, but at this point we will not make followup appointments for him per his request.  He verbalized understanding.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

